				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p>The experience in the rice sector highlights the ability of the EC to successfully run a managed trade regime, in the context of both the implementation of reform measures and the expansion of market access. This would appear to offer a model for the further reform of the EU sugar regime. Successfully maintaining a market balance, by supporting EU market prices, benefits ACP suppliers by improving the returns obtained from exporting to the EU.</p>
		</div>
		
